Ans.Variable

Q5.Datatypes impacts on memory allocation
Ans.true

Q6.public class Test_Variable {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int value = 10;
        int value1=”java”;
        System.out.println(value);
        System.out.println(value1);
    }
}
Ans.Type mismatch(bacause here java is declared as int)

Q7.Variable name is case-sensitive.
Ans.true

Q8.Space is permitted in variable name.
Ans.false

Q9.What is the range of short?
Ans.-32,768 to 32,767

Q10.Which suffix is used while declaring a long data type?
Ans.L

Q11.public class TestIntDataType{
public static void main(String[] args){
    byte value = -128;
    System.out.println(value);
    }
}
Ans.it gives -128 as output

Q12.
public class TestFloat{
public static void main(String[] args){
    int number1= 10.128952248;
    float number2 = 10.128952248f;
    double number3 = 10.128952248d;
 
    System.out.println(number1);
    System.out.println(number2);
    System.out.println(number3);
    }
}
Ans.It gives compite time error because float number1 is declared as int

Q13.What is Precision of float type variable?
Ans.7

Q14.Identify the data type with the following sentences:
1.The length should be one
2. Enclosed between quotes
3. Any character on the keyboard is allowed
Ans.char

Q15.In Java, boolean datatype can be represented by 1 or 0.
Ans.false(it represented by true or false)

Q16.How to cast 64-bit datatype into 32-bit datatype?
Ans.Exxplicit typecasting

Q17.In implicit Typecasting, what is the correct sequence of data type compatibility?
Ans.byte->short->int->long->float->double

Q18.In Java, we can create BigDecimal objects of which of the following types?
Ans.int.long,character array,string,double

Q19.The floating-point data types are used for calculating accurate precise values in a financial calculation.
Ans.true

Q20.BigDecimal is a part of which Java package?
